; An active experiment is an experiment that is currently ongoing or has not been marked as completed or cancelled; 
; The total file size is the sum of the average file sizes for each experiment type; 
; The average versions per type is the average number of versions for each experiment type; 
; The count of experiments per status is the number of experiments for each status within a type.

- "Latest versions" refers to the most recent version of each experiment, based on the version number; 
- "Cumulative wild-type and mutant-type cell counts" refer to the total counts of wild-type and mutant-type cells, respectively, up to a given time point; 
- "Latest access dates" refer to the most recent dates on which the experiments were accessed.

sql:
SELECT experiment_id, SUM(wt_cells) AS total_wt_cells
FROM experiment_details
GROUP BY experiment_id;

SELECT wt_cells
FROM experiment_details
WHERE experiment_id = 1;
